{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-page-js","path":"/projects/odundo/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>A very simple and again last minute Fitzwilliam Museum digital intervention. The Director requested\nthe labels, text and audio for the exhibition to be put online a few days before opening. The problem was simple:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>15 cases</li>\n<li>Multiple objects in each case</li>\n<li>Cases had label text for example <a href=\"https://fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/visit-us/exhibitions/magdalene-odundo-in-cambridge/cases/case-2\">Case 2</a></li>\n<li>Objects had <a href=\"https://fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/visit-us/exhibitions/labels/teapot-with-cane-handle\">label text</a> and <a href=\"https://fitzmuseum.cam.ac.uk/conversations/podcasts/magdalene-odundo-audio-series\">audio files</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Pull these together!</p>\n<p>To do this, a custom table was created in Directus and content uploaded and pulled back through the API. This provided\nreusable content structure for any other exhibitions that might be created in the future that had many-to-many\nrelationships for cases, object and labels.</p>","id":"612d81a7-f65f-5b1f-9bcc-970b618c687d","timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":104},"frontmatter":{"date":"October 29, 2019","section":"projects","title":"Magdalene Odundo in Cambridge - a digital archive","description":"A digital archive of the work of Magdalene Odundo in Cambridge","role":null,"partners":null,"collaborators":["George Doji","Helen Ritchie"],"institution":"The Fitzwilliam Museum","publications":null,"geo_lat":52.199722,"geo_lon":0.119167,"news":null,"background":{"id":"40b15c82-e3e3-5638-8f33-75c5e18c1bdc","absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/museologi.st/museologi.st/content/images/2021/gal_26_odundo_021_202110_mfj22_mas.jpeg","publicURL":"/static/7cfa62d1498c7fda4754a05201a81fcb/gal_26_odundo_021_202110_mfj22_mas.jpeg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#c8c8d8","images":{"fallb